# TypeScript

## Const Types Pattern (REQUIRED)
```typescript
// ✅ ALWAYS: Create const object first, then extract type
const STATUS = {
  ACTIVE: "active",
  INACTIVE: "inactive",
  PENDING: "pending",
} as const;

type Status = (typeof STATUS)[keyof typeof STATUS];

// ❌ NEVER: Direct union types
type Status = "active" | "inactive" | "pending";
```

## Flat Interfaces (REQUIRED)
```typescript
// ✅ ALWAYS: One level depth
interface UserAddress {
  street: string;
  city: string;
}

interface User {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  address: UserAddress;
}

// ❌ NEVER: Inline nested objects
interface User {
  address: { street: string; city: string };
}
```

## Never Use `any`
```typescript
// ✅ Use unknown
declare const input: unknown;

// ✅ Use generics
function first<T>(arr: T[]): T | undefined;

// ❌ NEVER
function parse(input: any): any;
```

## Utility Types
```typescript
Pick<User, "id" | "name">     // Select fields
Omit<User, "id">              // Exclude fields
Partial<User>                 // All optional
Required<User>                // All required
Readonly<User>                // All readonly
Record<string, User>          // Object type
ReturnType<typeof fn>         // Function return type
Parameters<typeof fn>         // Function params tuple
```

## Type Guards
```typescript
function isUser(value: unknown): value is User {
  return (
    typeof value === "object" &&
    value !== null &&
    "id" in value &&
    "name" in value
  );
}
```

## Import Types
```typescript
import type { User } from "./types";
import { createUser, type Config } from "./utils";
```

## Repository layout (`/app`, `/core`, `/tests`)

For folder layout, no barrels, colocated domain tests under `core/<Entity>/logic/__tests__/`, and what belongs in `/tests` vs `/core`, read **`.cursor/skills/project-structure/SKILL.md`**.

For TypeScript conventions specific to **`/core`** (types vs constants, `XxxParams`, path imports), read **`.cursor/skills/typescript/SKILL.md`** in addition to this rule.
